The '''2nd parallel north''' is a [[circle of latitude]] that is 2 [[degree (angle)|degrees]] [[true north|north]] of the [[Earth|Earth's]] [[equator|equatorial plane]]. It crosses the [[Atlantic Ocean]], [[Africa]], the [[Indian Ocean]], [[Southeast Asia]], the [[Pacific Ocean]] and [[South America]].

==Around the world==
Starting at the [[Prime Meridian]] and heading eastwards, the parallel 2° north passes through:

