'''Jalkr''' is a bright crater on [[Jupiter]]'s [[natural satellite|moon]] [[Callisto (moon)|Callisto]] measuring 74&nbsp;km across (in the lower part of the image). This an example of a central dome [[impact crater]].<ref name="Greeley 2000">{{cite journal| last=Greeley| first=R.| title=Galileo views of the geology of Callisto|journal=Planetary and Space Science| date=2000| volume=48| pages=829–853| doi=10.1016/S0032-0633(00)00050-7| bibcode=2000P&SS...48..829G| author2=Klemaszewski, J.E.| author3=Wagner L.| issue=9| author4=the Galileo Imaging Team}}</ref> A smaller degraded crater in the upper part of the image is called '''Audr'''.

